  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, the monsoon is starting today — I’m a tea person, so I’ll be sipping chai by the window. How was your day at work?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Work was busy, as usual. I fixed a bug in our payment gateway — phew! I’m more of a coffee person, but today I tried a cup of tea to feel the monsoon vibe. It was... okay. Not my favorite, but I’ll give it a second try."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Work sounds intense — fixing payment bugs is no small task! Coffee to tea is a big switch, but you're giving it a fair shot. What made you try tea today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, it was your idea from last time that made me think about it. Also, my teammate keeps saying tea is better for the weather. Maybe I’ll try it again tomorrow — with a little more sugar, maybe?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"That makes sense — we often take advice from our circle. Adding a bit of sugar sounds like a good plan. What kind of weather do you prefer for work?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I prefer cool weather like today — not too rainy, though! Sometimes the heat makes me sleepy at work. But if it’s not pouring, I’m all for it. Monsoon season is better than scorching summers, right? Aajkal garmi to bhut naakar hai."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — cool weather keeps energy up. 'Aajkal garmi to bhut naakar hai' — I agree! What do you do to stay fresh in the heat?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "In summer, I try to drink more water and take short breaks. Sometimes I eat a mango or something juicy — it helps. Oh, and I keep my desk fan on high! But honestly, I just count the days till monsoon comes."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Short breaks and juicy mangoes — smart moves. Monsoon waits for no one, but it’s coming! What’s your go-to monsoon snack?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, I usually have bhel puri or some street food when it rains. But honestly, nothing beats a hot pakora with tea. Even if it’s just for the vibe. But maybe I’ll try some healthier option this time — like roasted chana or something."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Pakoras and tea are a classic combo — I get the vibe! Trying roasted chana sounds like a fresh twist. Have you tried it before?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, I haven’t tried roasted chana yet, but I’ve seen people eat it at office canteens. It looks tasty and less oily, so I’m thinking of giving it a try. Maybe tomorrow’s tea break?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Great plan — tea breaks are the perfect time to try something new. Will you get it from the canteen or maybe make it at home?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I'll go to the canteen first — it's easier and I can try different flavors. If I like it, maybe I'll try making it at home. But for now, I'll stick to their mix. Gotta go now — my team needs me. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Fair enough — canteen first, home later. Work calls, so off you go! Tell me how the roasted chana tastes tomorrow.\""
    }
  ],
